1
00:00:40,267 --> 00:00:41,133
<i> Didang?</i>

2
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:43,233
<i> Why do you look so tense?</i>

3
00:00:43,367 --> 00:00:44,433
<i> Call Manuel!</i>

4
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:45,267
<i> I don't want to!</i>

5
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:46,267
<i> Is that so?</i>

6
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:46,967
<i> Hello, Bro.</i>

7
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:48,233
<i> You're unbelievable!</i>

8
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:50,733
<i>You made your wife and children
suffer for two decades!</i>

9
00:00:50,867 --> 00:00:51,733
<i> That's enough.</i>

10
00:00:51,867 --> 00:00:53,467
<i>I want to teach
your so-called BFF!</i>

11
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:56,867
<i>That jerk is using his child
with Hazel</i>

12
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,100
<i> to ask for help from Felma!</i>

13
00:01:00,233 --> 00:01:00,900
<i> It's important...</i>

14
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:02,267
<i> Excuse me. And who are you?</i>

15
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:03,867
<i> I'm the unit owner.</i>

16
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,067
<i>You can be an accessory
to my husband's crime.</i>

17
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,600
<i>Were you in cahoots with Manuel
in kidnapping my child?</i>

18
00:01:08,767 --> 00:01:10,733
<i> Didang, I'll just eat here.</i>

19
00:01:10,867 --> 00:01:11,867
<i> I'll join you.</i>

20
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,800
<i> And I'll take you to school.</i>

21
00:01:13,933 --> 00:01:14,867
<i> Hello!</i>

22
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,200
<i> Juicy morning, FMP buddy.</i>

23
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:19,733
<i>This is Stephanie Lim
from Value More.</i>

24
00:01:19,867 --> 00:01:21,667
<i> At your service, yes?</i>

25
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:25,000
<i>We would like to send a VIP
invite for Miss Felma Ruiz.</i>

26
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:27,233
<i>May I ask for her home address?</i>

27
00:01:27,367 --> 00:01:28,133
<i> Felma-flirt!</i>

28
00:01:28,267 --> 00:01:29,900
<i> How did you get in here?</i>

29
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:31,633
<i> I'll sue you for trespassing!</i>

30
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:32,667
<i> That's what you deserve!</i>

31
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:33,767
<i> What now?</i>

32
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:34,300
<i> That's what you get!</i>

33
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:35,433
<i> Mom!</i>

34
00:01:35,567 --> 00:01:36,733
<i> Mom, stop, please!</i>

35
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:40,300
<i> Leave!</i>

36
00:01:40,467 --> 00:01:41,833
<i> I'll come back for you!</i>

37
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:43,600
<i>Let's bring her to the hospital.</i>

38
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:46,067
Sir, be careful on the ramp.

39
00:01:49,867 --> 00:01:51,000
Careful, Dad.

40
00:01:51,133 --> 00:01:52,567
If something bad happens
to Coleen,

41
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:54,100
or if she goes after Felma again

42
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:55,233
Jessica, I'm sorry,

43
00:01:55,367 --> 00:01:57,867
but I don't know what I might do
to your mom.

44
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,233
Oh, don't worry, Sir.

45
00:02:00,367 --> 00:02:03,500
She's already banned
in the subdivision.

46
00:02:03,633 --> 00:02:04,533
Dad, let's go.

47
00:02:04,667 --> 00:02:06,533
Let's go back to the Airbnb.

48
00:02:06,667 --> 00:02:08,233
No, no. Not now.

49
00:02:08,367 --> 00:02:10,233
Your mom might go
straight there.

50
00:02:15,667 --> 00:02:16,533
Andrea is calling.

51
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,333
Hello, Andrea?

52
00:02:20,467 --> 00:02:21,933
Hello, Didang!

53
00:02:22,067 --> 00:02:24,200
We've been trying to reach you,
but you haven't answered.

54
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,767
You, Mom, and Coleen.

55
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:28,167
We've been calling you.

56
00:02:28,300 --> 00:02:30,633
I'm sorry, Andrea.

57
00:02:30,767 --> 00:02:31,800
Something happened.

58
00:02:31,933 --> 00:02:34,167
What happened?

59
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:39,300
Hazel showed up
and went after Ma'am Felma.

60
00:02:39,433 --> 00:02:41,800
What is that Hazel doing there?

61
00:02:41,933 --> 00:02:43,167
What does she need?

62
00:02:48,033 --> 00:02:49,267
Stop fooling me, Didang.

63
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,767
That's not how
a busy tone sounds.

64
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:53,133
What really happened?

65
00:02:53,267 --> 00:02:55,000
They had a fight.

66
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:59,133
Ma'am Felma and that woman
had a fistfight.

67
00:02:59,267 --> 00:03:02,100
And Coleen even got
into an accident.

68
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:03,767
But it's all good now.

69
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:05,567
They're on their way back
from the hospital.

70
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:06,667
She only had a sprain.

71
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,000
So you don't have to worry.

72
00:03:08,133 --> 00:03:09,900
How can I not worry?

73
00:03:10,033 --> 00:03:12,700
Things like that are happening,
and we didn't even know a thing!

74
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:15,300
You should have called me
and Jeff!

75
00:03:15,433 --> 00:03:17,167
<i> Come on, Didang!</i>

76
00:03:32,133 --> 00:03:34,000
You shameless flirt!

77
00:03:34,133 --> 00:03:35,633
You went after Felma?

78
00:03:35,767 --> 00:03:40,400
Didn't I tell you my husband
and child are with Felma?

79
00:03:40,533 --> 00:03:43,100
That's why I went to visit them.

80
00:03:43,233 --> 00:03:45,333
So? Did you see them?

81
00:03:45,467 --> 00:03:46,167
No, right?

82
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,600
Because they weren't there!

83
00:03:48,733 --> 00:03:49,633
Well...

84
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:51,667
I didn't get to check
the whole house.

85
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,400
My fault.

86
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:54,467
It was annoying.

87
00:03:54,633 --> 00:03:57,000
I wasn't ready.
That's why they ganged up on me.

88
00:03:57,133 --> 00:04:00,733
But thank you for giving me
Felma's address.

89
00:04:00,867 --> 00:04:02,133
What are you talking about?

90
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:03,900
<i> Hi, this is Stephanie Lim.</i>

91
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:06,200
We're sending you 10,000 pesos
worth of gift certificates

92
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:07,733
<i> and VIP cards.</i>

93
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:12,433
<i> So that's all you're worth?</i>

94
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:14,800
How cheap!

95
00:04:14,933 --> 00:04:15,867
How dare you Hazel!

96
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:21,200
You're going to regret this!

97
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:23,267
Why are you talking
to Manuel's wife?

98
00:04:43,667 --> 00:04:44,667
Didang.

99
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:47,633
Dear, don't forget
what the doctor said.

100
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:49,867
Don't forget to take
your medicine on time

101
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,667
so your hand doesn't swell
or hurt, okay?

102
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:53,633
Yes, Mom.

103
00:04:53,767 --> 00:04:55,567
Okay, Coleen.

104
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:58,267
I'll go upstairs
so I can take a bath.

105
00:04:58,400 --> 00:04:59,067
Sure, Mom.

106
00:04:59,200 --> 00:04:59,900
I'll stay here for now.

107
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:01,533
I'll drink some water first.

108
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,400
You go ahead.

109
00:05:03,533 --> 00:05:05,667
Make sure you follow right after
so you can also take a bath.

110
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:06,633
Yes, Mom.

111
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:07,533
All right.

112
00:05:07,667 --> 00:05:08,433
Didang, you take care of things,
okay?

113
00:05:08,567 --> 00:05:09,633
Yes, Ma'am.

114
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:21,767
Hey, wait for me.

115
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:29,967
Coleen.

116
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,067
Jessica.

117
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,300
Dad.

118
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:37,000
Coleen, how's your hand?

119
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:38,333
It's okay.

120
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:39,800
You don't have to worry.

121
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:42,367
Sorry for what happened, Coleen.

122
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,467
Come on, Jessica.

123
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,900
What your mom did
isn't your fault.

124
00:05:50,533 --> 00:05:54,767
Dad, don't get frustrated.

125
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:56,067
It's not worth it.

126
00:05:58,767 --> 00:06:02,300
Dear, we have a favor to ask.

127
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:05,000
Can we leave tomorrow instead?

128
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:08,233
Hazel might still
be at the Airbnb.

129
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:10,033
Of course.

130
00:06:10,167 --> 00:06:12,333
You're very much welcome here.

131
00:06:12,467 --> 00:06:14,467
Stay as long as you want.

132
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,500
No, Coleen.

133
00:06:15,633 --> 00:06:18,567
Dad, the important thing
is that we stay careful.

134
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:21,533
Yes, but it's only
until tomorrow anyway.

135
00:06:21,667 --> 00:06:24,167
Sorry, it's just that
the situation is really tough

136
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,367
right now.

137
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:27,733
Okay.

138
00:06:29,633 --> 00:06:31,433
But for now, Dad,

139
00:06:31,567 --> 00:06:34,900
let's try to forget
about our problems for a while.

140
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:39,667
Let's make the most
of our time together.

141
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:42,100
Coleen, what do you have
in mind?

142
00:06:42,267 --> 00:06:44,067
I'm sneaking in tonight

143
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,600
so we can sleep
next to each other.

144
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:48,133
I love that!

145
00:06:48,267 --> 00:06:49,900
I also like that.

146
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:51,567
When I left,
you were still so small.

147
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:55,233
All I could do was just lullaby
you to sleep.

148
00:06:55,367 --> 00:06:59,200
But now, I'm finally
able to hug you while you sleep.

149
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:02,233
Dad.

150
00:07:05,667 --> 00:07:07,133
I love you, Dad.

151
00:07:07,267 --> 00:07:08,733
I love you too, Coleen.

152
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,133
Don't squeeze my hand too tight,
Dad.

153
00:07:11,267 --> 00:07:12,000
It hurts.

154
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:14,233
Oh, sorry, sorry.

155
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:17,600
Noah, I'm sorry.

156
00:07:17,733 --> 00:07:19,433
Let me explain.

157
00:07:19,567 --> 00:07:22,300
I'm helping Hazel.

158
00:07:22,433 --> 00:07:26,000
I'm helping Hazel
to get Manuel back,

159
00:07:26,133 --> 00:07:27,467
so she can bring him home
to Canada.

160
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:30,167
So she won't bother
Felma anymore.

161
00:07:30,300 --> 00:07:32,000
Please, Noah, I'm begging you.

162
00:07:32,133 --> 00:07:33,000
Don't expose me.

163
00:07:33,133 --> 00:07:35,533
Please, please, please.

164
00:07:35,667 --> 00:07:37,000
No.

165
00:07:37,133 --> 00:07:39,533
In fact, I will help you.

166
00:07:39,667 --> 00:07:42,833
I also want Manuel
to go back to Canada.

167
00:07:42,967 --> 00:07:45,100
Thank you. Thank you, Noah.

168
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,933
But Felma might take it
the wrong way.

169
00:07:51,567 --> 00:07:53,900
She might say again
that I'm meddling in her life.

170
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:55,067
Let's not tell her.

171
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,167
Let's keep this between us.

172
00:08:00,433 --> 00:08:01,333
Wait, Noah.

173
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:03,300
I can see that you're thinking.

174
00:08:03,433 --> 00:08:03,967
Stop it.

175
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:04,967
Stop.

176
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,300
Stop thinking too much.

177
00:08:06,433 --> 00:08:07,700
Action, action, action!

178
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:08,967
Don't say I didn't warn you.

179
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:12,800
That tiny bit of hope
you have with Felma

180
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:14,233
might just suddenly
rest in peace.

181
00:08:14,367 --> 00:08:15,767
Like that.

182
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:17,133
No.

183
00:08:17,267 --> 00:08:18,600
I won't let that happen.

184
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:22,100
I will help you.

185
00:08:25,667 --> 00:08:29,467
But, Paz, I'm wondering...

186
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,500
Could Felma be hiding Manuel?

187
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:39,500
- Felma?
- Didang?

188
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:41,700
- Let's prepare the food.
- Felma!

189
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:42,867
Who...

190
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:43,800
- Hi!
- Paz.

191
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:48,200
What's going on?

192
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:50,367
Paz, Noah, why are you here?

193
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:52,867
We're worried for you.

194
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,833
Coleen, how's your hand?

195
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,200
It still hurts a bit, Jeff,

196
00:08:57,333 --> 00:09:00,600
but it's getting better.

197
00:09:00,733 --> 00:09:03,433
Felma, I think you need
additional security.

198
00:09:03,567 --> 00:09:04,767
Would you like me to hire
a security guard

199
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:06,533
to watch the gate?

200
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:08,800
Thank you, Noah, but I'm okay.

201
00:09:08,933 --> 00:09:11,600
Hazel has been reported
to the guard house.

202
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:14,833
I'm sure she can no longer get
inside the subdivision again.

203
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:17,800
Mom, why did you let Hazel
get away?

204
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:19,567
You should have gotten her
arrested!

205
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:20,567
Let's just leave it be.

206
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:21,633
It has already happened.

207
00:09:21,767 --> 00:09:22,867
No, Mom. She came here!

208
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,433
We must sue her!

209
00:09:24,567 --> 00:09:26,200
Andrea is right, Mom.

210
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:27,733
What for?

211
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,633
I don't want any trouble.

212
00:09:29,767 --> 00:09:31,567
What if she doesn't stop, Mom?

213
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:33,767
What if she storms the office?

214
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:35,933
Where is your ex, anyway?

215
00:09:36,067 --> 00:09:37,433
I don't know.

216
00:09:37,567 --> 00:09:39,367
Are you sure, Mom?

217
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:40,767
Don't you really know?

218
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:41,667
Why?

219
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:44,067
Do you think I'm hiding Manuel?

220
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,333
It's not like that, Mom.

221
00:09:45,467 --> 00:09:47,667
But Hazel wouldn't storm in
if you didn't know anything.

222
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:50,533
Why would I hide Manuel?

223
00:09:50,667 --> 00:09:51,767
It's not like that, Felma.

224
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:55,667
Maybe he just came to you
for help?

225
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,133
Just tell us, Felma.

226
00:09:57,267 --> 00:09:59,400
So we can help.

227
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:01,533
Hold on!

228
00:10:01,700 --> 00:10:04,800
Why are you ganging up on me?

229
00:10:04,933 --> 00:10:06,600
No, Felma.

230
00:10:06,733 --> 00:10:09,267
I don't know where Manuel is!

231
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:12,433
And more importantly,
I'm not hiding him!

232
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:17,433
I'm done here!

233
00:10:17,567 --> 00:10:18,133
Move!

234
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:41,533
Later, your sister will lie
between us, okay?

235
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:42,833
Yes, Dad.

236
00:10:56,433 --> 00:11:01,267
Dad, there really isn't
a cheaper apartment anymore.

237
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,400
I'm starting to not
want to take it.

238
00:11:03,533 --> 00:11:07,400
Oh, but we really need
to leave this place.

239
00:11:07,533 --> 00:11:09,200
So we won't always be anxious.

240
00:11:09,367 --> 00:11:11,967
And besides, Coleen might
get hurt if we stay.

241
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:16,200
Dear, can I borrow your phone?

242
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:19,067
Maybe we can stay
at your Uncle Abel's.

243
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,167
Hello, Bro.

244
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:28,467
Hello, Bro.

245
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:32,000
Can we stay there?

246
00:11:34,033 --> 00:11:36,133
Bro, you can't stay here.

247
00:11:36,267 --> 00:11:39,000
Paz is already mad at me.

248
00:11:39,133 --> 00:11:40,167
She's bothering me.

249
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,633
She wants to know where you are.

250
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:46,867
<i>Wait, where are you and Jessica?</i>

251
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:51,300
Bro, I'm only telling you this
because I trust you, okay?

252
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:57,100
We're here at Felma's house.

253
00:11:57,233 --> 00:11:58,600
<i> Coleen hid us.</i>

254
00:11:58,733 --> 00:12:01,067
What?

255
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:04,600
Is that why Paz said
that Hazel stormed in there

256
00:12:04,733 --> 00:12:06,433
<i> and wants to catch you?</i>

257
00:12:06,567 --> 00:12:09,000
Yes, that's why we need
to leave immediately

258
00:12:09,133 --> 00:12:11,200
<i> before the trouble explodes.</i>

259
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:13,700
Bro, you really can't stay here.

260
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:14,867
I also can't let you.

261
00:12:15,033 --> 00:12:16,733
Paz has thrown
hurtful words at you, right?

262
00:12:16,867 --> 00:12:18,933
<i>And I'm sorry for what she did.</i>

263
00:12:19,067 --> 00:12:21,333
But I'll go out tomorrow.

264
00:12:21,467 --> 00:12:22,933
I'll find you a cheap apartment.

265
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:27,167
Okay, Bro. Thank you.

266
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:29,367
Okay. Be careful, okay?

267
00:12:33,767 --> 00:12:36,867
Dear, let's just take
that apartment you saw,

268
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,533
even if it's a bit expensive.

269
00:12:38,667 --> 00:12:40,867
We really need to leave
this place.

270
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,200
Okay.

271
00:12:45,267 --> 00:12:49,967
But Dad, I'll go back
to the Airbnb on my own.

272
00:12:53,933 --> 00:12:58,600
Noah, I really hope I'm wrong.

273
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:06,333
Felma is telling the truth.

274
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:07,833
We both know her, Paz.

275
00:13:10,133 --> 00:13:15,167
She would not get that angry
if she were lying.

276
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:18,633
I just really hope
we find Manuel soon.

277
00:13:18,767 --> 00:13:24,967
So I can shove him to the throat
of her demon-looking wife!

278
00:13:25,133 --> 00:13:28,233
So that Felma and her children
will be at peace.

279
00:13:28,367 --> 00:13:31,000
Maybe it's better if we just
leave them be for now.

280
00:13:36,033 --> 00:13:37,200
Mom?

281
00:13:37,333 --> 00:13:38,900
Let's not bother Mom anymore.

282
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:41,733
I'll just talk to her.

283
00:13:41,867 --> 00:13:43,733
She's mad, isn't she?

284
00:13:43,867 --> 00:13:45,433
It's your fault.

285
00:13:45,567 --> 00:13:46,933
You can't control your mouth.

286
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,567
Me?

287
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,600
Am I the only one?

288
00:13:51,733 --> 00:13:53,133
You know, if you had
talked to Mom properly,

289
00:13:53,267 --> 00:13:54,433
this wouldn't have happened.

290
00:13:56,367 --> 00:13:57,567
Fine!

291
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:02,933
I should have talked
to her better.

292
00:14:03,067 --> 00:14:05,433
I was just worried, that's all.

293
00:14:05,567 --> 00:14:07,900
That Hazel stormed at Mom.

294
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,833
What if she didn't
just hurt Mom?

295
00:14:12,967 --> 00:14:16,467
What if in her craziness,
she actually killed Mom?

296
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:21,467
So if Mom knows
where that man is...

297
00:14:23,633 --> 00:14:24,733
I'll get involved.

298
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,367
I'll make sure he goes back
to his wife.

299
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:34,167
So I could protect Mom.

300
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:36,500
Coleen, do you know anything?

301
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:37,467
I don't, Jeff.

302
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:39,167
Are you and Mom
keeping a secret?

303
00:14:41,667 --> 00:14:43,767
Mom doesn't know where Dad is.

304
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,000
You also.

305
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:48,967
I'm serious.

306
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:52,333
If you don't stop
what you're doing,

307
00:14:52,467 --> 00:14:54,900
you'll lose a sister.

308
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,400
<i> They're asleep.</i>

309
00:15:21,533 --> 00:15:23,900
<i>I will show you something
when I come downstairs.</i>

310
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:37,733
<i> Okay.</i>

311
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:41,000
<i> Whatever that is, I'm excited.</i>

312
00:15:41,133 --> 00:15:42,900
<i> Please be careful.</i>

313
00:16:15,467 --> 00:16:16,833
Is your sister
already coming here?

314
00:16:58,800 --> 00:16:59,800
Coleen...

315
00:17:02,067 --> 00:17:04,800
I know the pain you're feeling.

316
00:17:04,933 --> 00:17:07,200
The longing you have
for your father.

317
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:12,133
I know how much
you want to see him.

318
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:24,500
But it's just not possible
anymore.

319
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:31,833
So, Coleen...

320
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:37,467
Let Mom be the one
to hold you now, okay?

321
00:17:42,933 --> 00:17:43,867
<i> Manuel,</i>

322
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,500
<i> wherever you and Jessica are,</i>

323
00:17:49,100 --> 00:17:50,567
<i> I hope you are safe.</i>

324
00:17:56,067 --> 00:17:59,167
I thought your sister
was already coming down?

325
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:00,733
I also thought so, Dad.

326
00:18:00,867 --> 00:18:03,333
But she didn't reply anymore.

327
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:05,133
Let's just wait for her.

328
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:15,367
Maybe it's better
if we go to sleep, Jessica.

329
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:23,167
<i> Jessica,</i>

330
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:27,033
<i> please tell Dad I'm sorry.</i>

331
00:20:27,167 --> 00:20:30,500
<i>Mom went into my room.
She slept next to me.</i>

332
00:21:32,033 --> 00:21:33,933
Classmate!

333
00:21:34,067 --> 00:21:35,433
Long time no see.

334
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:39,000
When was the last time?

335
00:21:39,133 --> 00:21:41,000
High school graduation?

336
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:43,133
You've changed so much!

337
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:44,633
You look beautiful!

338
00:21:44,767 --> 00:21:46,433
Let's get down to business.

339
00:21:46,567 --> 00:21:48,800
You've got perfect timing,
classmate.

340
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:51,533
I just took an early retirement.

341
00:21:51,667 --> 00:21:53,500
Oh, please, Maximo.

342
00:21:53,633 --> 00:21:55,700
Don't butter me up.

343
00:21:55,833 --> 00:21:57,567
Early retirement.

344
00:21:57,700 --> 00:21:59,233
I know you were dismissed
from service

345
00:21:59,367 --> 00:22:02,067
because of all your illegal
activities.

346
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:04,533
So what job do you want me
to do?

347
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:10,000
I want you to find them.

348
00:22:10,133 --> 00:22:11,367
These two.

349
00:22:19,867 --> 00:22:22,733
Jeff, have you already
talked to Mom?

350
00:22:22,867 --> 00:22:25,300
Not yet.
Didang said she went jogging.

351
00:22:25,433 --> 00:22:28,867
We know that when she jogs,
it means she's stressed.

352
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,933
I know. That's why I don't
feel like going.

353
00:22:31,067 --> 00:22:32,933
Mom needs us here.

354
00:22:33,067 --> 00:22:35,633
You promised Tetay this day.

355
00:22:35,767 --> 00:22:38,233
My niece is already expecting.

356
00:22:38,367 --> 00:22:39,167
It's the weekend.

357
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:40,133
Why don't you just skip work?

358
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:42,400
I can't do that.

359
00:22:42,533 --> 00:22:47,133
I need to check on our outlets
so I can monitor the sales.

360
00:22:47,267 --> 00:22:50,600
You two, don't worry
about Ma'am Felma.

361
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:53,500
I invited her
to go to the market,

362
00:22:53,633 --> 00:22:56,067
do groceries, get a massage,

363
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:57,533
and join a yoga class
at the clubhouse,

364
00:22:57,667 --> 00:22:59,367
even though I don't even know
how to do yoga!

365
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:01,467
So don't worry, I've got this.

366
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:02,567
Go!

367
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:04,000
- Thank you, Didang.
- You're the best, Didang.

368
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:05,600
- Thank you!
- See?

369
00:23:05,733 --> 00:23:07,067
- I told you.
- Bye.

370
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,300
Be safe.

371
00:23:08,433 --> 00:23:09,367
Look after Mom, okay?

372
00:23:09,500 --> 00:23:10,900
Yes.

373
00:23:11,033 --> 00:23:12,067
Text me, okay?

374
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:14,300
Tell me what food you like
so I can cook it.

375
00:23:14,433 --> 00:23:15,300
Okay, Didang.

376
00:23:15,433 --> 00:23:16,467
Bye, Didang.

377
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:18,667
- Be safe here, okay?
- Be safe.

378
00:23:37,667 --> 00:23:38,967
- Didang.
- They're gone.

379
00:23:39,100 --> 00:23:40,600
Did you book a ride?

380
00:23:40,733 --> 00:23:42,033
Yes. It's already waiting
outside.

381
00:23:42,167 --> 00:23:45,267
Okay, go. Be safe, okay?

382
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:48,500
And don't forget to text me
when you're on your way back.

383
00:23:48,633 --> 00:23:49,800
Thank you, Didang.

384
00:23:49,933 --> 00:23:51,733
Please look after Dad.

385
00:23:51,867 --> 00:23:52,900
He's still sleeping.

386
00:23:53,033 --> 00:23:55,100
Don't worry about him.
I got him.

387
00:23:55,267 --> 00:23:55,967
Text me.

388
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:57,600
I will. Thank you.

389
00:24:04,533 --> 00:24:06,800
Jessica?

390
00:24:06,933 --> 00:24:09,533
Jessica?

391
00:24:09,667 --> 00:24:10,767
Jessica!

392
00:24:14,733 --> 00:24:15,967
Was that Jessica?

393
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:19,667
Did I see it wrong?

394
00:24:25,533 --> 00:24:27,133
Didang?

395
00:24:27,267 --> 00:24:28,900
Didang!

396
00:24:29,067 --> 00:24:30,233
Where are you?

397
00:24:30,367 --> 00:24:31,033
Didang?

398
00:24:33,267 --> 00:24:34,433
Didang!

399
00:24:34,567 --> 00:24:35,067
Ma'am?

400
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:37,600
Why aren't you answering?

401
00:24:37,733 --> 00:24:41,967
Ma'am, why did you
come back so soon?

402
00:24:42,100 --> 00:24:43,967
I forgot my water jug.

403
00:24:45,867 --> 00:24:47,333
But you know what? It's like...

404
00:24:47,467 --> 00:24:49,500
It's kind of weird.

405
00:24:49,633 --> 00:24:54,500
I think I saw Manuel's
daughter, Jessica.

406
00:24:54,633 --> 00:24:55,967
It looked like
she came from here.

407
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,933
Why do you have so much food?

408
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:05,467
Where are you taking that?

409
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:07,200
Who is it for?

410
00:25:07,333 --> 00:25:09,167
This is for me, Ma'am.

411
00:25:09,300 --> 00:25:12,067
I'm planning to eat
in the laundry area.

412
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:15,000
I want to eat
while doing the laundry.

413
00:25:15,133 --> 00:25:16,567
That much food?

414
00:25:16,700 --> 00:25:18,033
You're with someone, aren't you?

415
00:25:20,167 --> 00:25:21,800
I'm just really hungry, Ma'am.

416
00:25:21,933 --> 00:25:23,833
I didn't eat dinner last night,
remember?

417
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:30,367
Didang, was it Jessica
I saw earlier?

418
00:25:37,967 --> 00:25:39,467
Guard, good morning.

419
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:44,167
Miss Claire said that my mom
didn't come back anymore.

420
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:45,533
She didn't.

421
00:25:45,667 --> 00:25:47,367
Thank you.

422
00:25:47,500 --> 00:25:49,667
Ma'am Jessica, every problem
can be solved

423
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:51,867
through a sincere conversation.

424
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,167
I hope everything
will be all right.

425
00:25:54,300 --> 00:25:57,600
Mom, there are rats
and cockroaches there.

426
00:25:57,733 --> 00:25:59,233
Have you been there?

427
00:25:59,367 --> 00:26:00,233
Did you go inside?

428
00:26:01,867 --> 00:26:04,000
Don't stop me
from doing what I want!

429
00:26:04,133 --> 00:26:05,300
I'm right!

430
00:26:05,433 --> 00:26:06,633
Manuel is here, isn't he?

431
00:26:06,767 --> 00:26:07,500
You two!

432
00:26:07,633 --> 00:26:09,133
- Mom! Mom!
- Manuel!

433
00:26:09,300 --> 00:26:10,133
Hello?

434
00:26:10,267 --> 00:26:12,033
Ma'am Jessica has arrived.

435
00:26:12,167 --> 00:26:12,967
She's on her way up.

436
00:26:13,100 --> 00:26:14,833
Guard, thank you.

437
00:26:14,967 --> 00:26:17,067
I'm finally going
to see my child.

438
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:17,833
<i>- Mom!
- Manuel!</i>

439
00:26:17,967 --> 00:26:19,500
<i>- Mom!
- Manuel!</i>

440
00:26:19,633 --> 00:26:20,933
<i> I'll go!</i>

441
00:26:24,500 --> 00:26:25,367
Manuel!

442
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:28,933
You really are here!
